@slaweksiluk The `receive` call in wishbone_master will also delete the message for `request_msg` used in the previous iteration. This is a convenience when you have a simple "single threaded" BFM. In your case the message is placed in a queue and it shouldn't be deleted until it has been used on the other side of the queue. You can replace `receive` with the following and then delete the message manually when it's no longer needed.

``` vhdl
      -- receive(net, bus_handle.p_actor, request_msg);
      wait_for_message(net, bus_handle.p_actor, status);
      get_message(net, bus_handle.p_actor, request_msg);
```

where status is of `com_status_t`. You can ignore the status. It's only useful to determine a timeout if you add a timeout parameter to the `get_message` call

